          <h2>Product quantity display</h2>
          <hr />

          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>The number of units to purchase (i.e. quantity or voucher amount). </p>
            <h4>Interactions</h4>
            <p>Users can alter the product amount to determine either the quantity of units they wish to purchase, or the value in vouchers they wish to exchange.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <p>Only common styles are loaded for this component.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common-components/value-calculator.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Use of Javascript</h3>
            <p>JavaScript is used to add + and - buttons alongside the input. These buttons automatically increment/decrement the value according to the defined incremental value.</p>
            <p>The required voucher total is updated in realtime when altering quantities.</p>
            <p>The user is prevented from entering a non-numeric value.</p>
            <p>Inputs must specify a class of 'quantity' or 'value' depending on the value type.</p>
            <p>Inputs may specify attributes to control the behaviour:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>data-unit-value - the voucher value of one unit</li>
              <li>data-step - the amount to increase/decrease the value when a button is clicked</li>
              <li>data-min - the minimum value</li>
              <li>data-max - the maximum value</li>
              <li>data-precision - number of decimal palces to format the value</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The buttons are disabled if minimum or maximum values are reached.</p>
            <h4>Non-JS behaviour</h4>
            <p>The + and - buttons are not shown. The text input defaults to be a standard input field that the user can enter any value in to.</p>
            <p><em>see figure 1</em></p>
            <p class="styleguide-img">
              <img src="../img/styleguide/quantity.png" alt="non-javascript view of amend quantity layout">
            </p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>There are two variants relating to fixed price (purchase in full) products and money off products. We have also displayed an example of how this component might look if a non-javascript user has encountered an error when trying to submit the form with an incorrect quantity value.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Responsive Images</h3>
            <p>The +/- icons are CSS background images. No retina images are supplied as part of this phase but could be incorporated at a later date. </p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Accessibility</h3>
            <p>This element contains a form field. It requires a label/input pair with a correctly populated unique for/id value.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
